Hotter 'N Hell Hundred
description: Hotter \\\\\\\'N Hell Hundred features criteriums for Pro/Cat. 1-2 men and Pro/Cat. 1-2-3 women on Friday evening, Aug. 22, 2008, and road races of various distances for all. categories on Saturday, Aug. 23. See attached flyer for details. Flyer contains complete information on all categories.
course: The criteriums take place on a closed circuit in downtown Wichita Falls. The road races take place within rolling closures on point-to-point courses.
registration: Registration takes place online at www.hh100.org, by mail and on-site. Complete details are in the race flyer.
notes: Complete details are in the race flyer and also in a race manual that will be distributed at registration and online.
directions: The criterium start is at Fourth and Lamar streets in downtown Wichita Falls. The road race starts will be staaged at Scott and Lincoln streets in downtown Wichita Falls. Complete details will be in the race manual.

title: Camp Eagle Classic Mountain Bike Festival
Camp Eagle Classic Mountain Bike Festival
Rocky Hill Roundup Short Track
description: Short track exhibition type races for all categories.
course: Course will be about 1.5 miles around the front part of the ranch.
registration: Prereg at Bikereg.com or register at the ranch on raceday up to 30 minutes before your race.
notes: Must have USA Cycling MTB race to enter. One day non license fee of $5 is available for all but the Cat 1 race.
directions: Rocky Hill Ranch in on FM 153 two miles north of HWY 71 in Smithville, TX.

title: Sun and Ski Sports Presents the Rocky Hill Roundup
description: Season finale of the TMBRA Fall Cup.
course: We will be using the 9 mile course of Rocky Hill Ranch, number of laps varies by category, shortened course for 12 and unders.
registration: Register online with BikeReg.com or mail in form available at TMBRA.org
notes: Rocky Hill Ranch is open year round for riding, race course will be marked by the weekend prior to the race. Saloon is now open for food and drinks. Primitive camping available on site. Pre-entry fee is $30 for adults, $15 for Juniors 13-18, $10 for Juniors 12 and under. Onsite is $5 more for adults.
directions: Rocky Hill Ranch is in Smithville Texas, on FM 153 just north of State Hwy 71.
